I"ú<h2 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
  <li>2 cups 00 flour</li>
  <li>1 tsp salt</li>
  <li>1 cup warm water</li>
  <li>1 tsp yeast</li>
  <li>1 tsp sugar</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="method">Method</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Mix water, yeast and sugar and let stand for five minutes (bubbles!).</li>
  <li>Stir together flour and salt and make a hole.</li>
  <li>Pour in liquid and work in slowly with fingers/something. Might need some extra flour.</li>
  <li>Get onto a floured workspace and knead a few minutes.</li>
  <li>Place in a lightly oiled bowl and let stand (covered) for 30 minutes.</li>
  <li>Cut into about 4 pieces, depending on your pizza-size preference.</li>
  <li>Use immediately, or wrap into individual plastic-covered balls and refrigerate.</li>
</ul>
